This paper is about improving the efficiency of diversification methods for web search results. The paper discusses a new methodology for detecting when and how query results need to be diversified, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also compares and evaluates different diversification methods, which involves algorithms and data structures, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with scalability issues, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
